name L/B Wedding Cake
desc The cake served at Lyro and Borb's wedding. Two tiered matcha and szechuan
  pepper flavored sponge filled with white chocolate butter cream and with
  a white chocolate cream cheese frosting.
note <p>Serving amount (3) is for a two-tiered cake, with springforms sized
  26cm and 20cm respectively. For a single tier version, use a serving size
  of 2 for the 26cm version and a serving size of 1 for the 20cm version.</p>
  <p>Plan for two days: Bake sponge and prepare buttercream on the morning
  of day 1. In the evening, fill the sponge and refrigerate overnight.
  In the morning of day 2, frost with cream cheese frosting and refrigerate
  again briefly to solidify.</p>
  <p>Decorate to taste. We used dried peaflower.</p>
serves 3
tags cake

# Tier 1 Sponge (Matcha)

- 9 eggs
Split eggs.
-> egg whites for tier 1
-> egg yolks for tier 1

- 180 g sugar
@ egg whites for tier 1
Beat egg whites until somewhat stiffened, add the sugar and whip to stiff peaks.
-> egg foam for tier 1

- 180 g sugar
- 45 ml milk
- 75 g butter, softened
- salt
@ egg yolks for tier 1
Mix sugar, milk, butter, salt and egg yolks and beat until foamy.
-> egg cream for tier 1

- 255 g flour
- 60 g matcha
- 2 tsp baking powder
@ egg foam for tier 1
@ egg cream for tier 1
<p>Sift dry ingredients into egg yolks and incorporate well. Mix in {.333} of the egg white
to loosen batter. Then mix in remaining egg whites, about 20 seconds max with a handmixer.</p>
<p>Mix egg whites just enough to incorporate evenly. Folding is unnecessary though.</p>
<p>Bake for 60 minutes at 150°C (140°C fan). A cake belt can help to prevent doming.</p>

- 60 ml caramel syrup
- 150 ml green tea
Let cake cool, then cut in half horizontally and soak with caramel syrup and green tea.
-> tier 1 sponge


# Tier 2 Sponge (Szechuan Peppercorn)

- 6 eggs
Split eggs.
-> egg whites for tier 2
-> egg yolks for tier 2

- 120 g sugar
@ egg whites for tier 2
Beat egg whites until somewhat stiffened, add the sugar and whip to stiff peaks.
-> egg foam for tier 2

- 120 g sugar
- 30 ml milk
- 55 g butter, softened
- salt
@ egg yolks for tier 2
Mix sugar, milk, butter, salt and egg yolks and beat until foamy.
-> egg cream for tier 2

- 170 g flour
- 40 g cocoa
- 2 tsp baking powder
@ egg foam for tier 2
@ egg cream for tier 2
<p>Sift dry ingredients into egg yolks and incorporate well. Mix in ⅓ of the egg white
to loosen batter. Then mix in remaining egg whites, about 20 seconds max with a handmixer.</p>
<p>Mix egg whites just enough to incorporate evenly. Folding is unnecessary though.</p>
<p>Bake for 60 minutes at 150°C (140°C fan). A cake belt can help to prevent doming.</p>

- 1 tbsp szechuan peppercorn oil
- 50 ml caramel syrup
- 60 ml water
Let cake cool, then cut in half horizontally. Mix liquids until well emulsified and soak
sponge with them.
-> tier 2 sponge


# Buttercream

- 1000 g butter
Cut butter into small pieces.
-> butter for buttercream

- 800 g white chocolate
Melt chocolate.
-> white chocolate for buttercream

- 10 eggs
- 600 g sugar
- 240 ml water
@ butter for buttercream
@ white chocolate for buttercream
<p>Split {5} of the eggs and discard whites. In a bain marie, start whipping eggs. Bring
water and sugar to a high boil and drizzle into eggs. Continue whipping until eggs have
reached 65°C. Mix in butter and chocolate until incorporated, then refrigerate until set.</p>
<p><emph>Rescue note:</emph> If the buttercream does not set properly, add more white
chocolate.</p>
-> buttercream

= tier 1 sponge
= tier 2 sponge
= buttercream
Whip up buttercream. Fill both sponges with buttercream (at a 2:1 split). Refrigerate
again until set, preferably overnight.
-> filled sponges


# Frosting

- 500 g white chocolate
Melt chocolate.
-> white chocolate for frosting

- 600 g smooth cream cheese
- 200 g butter
- "dash of lemon juice"
- "dash of vanilla extract"
@ white chocolate for frosting
@ filled sponges
<p>Let cream cheese and butter come up to room temperature. Blend smooth. Fold in
chocolate, lemon juice and vanilla extract. Let cool slightly to make it easier to spread,
but do not let it set completely. If too cold, refrigerate in 30 second increments.</p>
<p>Frost first sponge tier. Set other tier on top and frost in place. Decorate and
refrigerate again.</p>
<p>Note that at this point, for the two tier version, the cake is very hard to transfer
without breaking up. I advise applying the frosting with the sponges already in the
container for transport.</p>
